If a man can’t fulfill his sexual demands from his partner then he is allowed to divorce her. Also, if a man enslaves her wife then she is also permitted to divorce her husband. However, the husband also has the right of divorce if his wife commits adultery.

The laws of divorce in Guinea Bissau are very strict and complicated to understand as there is a lot of confusion. As the Constitution prohibits divorce, it's also a very lengthy procedure, There are still around 30% divorces that take place in Guinea Bissau.

Traditional Guinean Matrimony Customs

The ceremonies of Guinean marriages are a lot similar to other cultures of Africa. There are different customs and traditions in various parts of Guinea Bissau. The preliminary marriage rituals start about one week before the wedding. After the civil registration of the two lovebirds, the wedding rituals take place at the bride’s house.
